{"Body":"<p>Since my 9 months old son started pointing to things and saying 'Ahh?' with a proper question intonation, I was wondering if all other languages have the same intonation for questions as in English (as in stressing the last word in the sentence). I am interested if it just comes naturally to human beings or is an acquired behaviour.  </p>\n", "Id":"1370", "LastEditorUserId":"444", "AcceptedAnswerId":"1372", "Title":"Intonation for questions in different languages and child's early language development intonations", "CreationDate":"2012-02-05T11:34:40.463", "OwnerUserId":"739", "PostTypeId":"1", "Tags":"<language-acquisition><intonation>", "AnswerCount":"1", "comments":[], "LastEditDate":"2012-02-05T18:01:38.487", "LastEditedUser":{"UpVotes":"127", "WebsiteUrl":"", "Location":"Netherlands", "Id":"444", "DownVotes":"2", "AccountId":"902812", "Views":"19", "Reputation":"934", "CreationDate":"2011-10-23T14:14:27.380", "DisplayName":"arjan", "LastAccessDate":"2014-01-14T14:07:55.473", "AboutMe":""}, "ViewCount":"297", "LastActivityDate":"2012-02-07T13:49:11.303", "Score":"3", "OwnerUser":{"UpVotes":"2", "WebsiteUrl":"http://au.linkedin.com/pub/daria-trainor/18/362/2b7", "Id":"739", "AccountId":"907133", "CreationDate":"2012-02-05T11:23:24.583", "AboutMe":"<p>Love to learn something new everyday</p>\n", "Age":"31", "Location":"Newcastle, Australia", "DownVotes":"0", "Views":"1", "Reputation":"118", "DisplayName":"Daria", "LastAccessDate":"2012-05-31T01:46:46.780"}}